If you run the P87TEST program that has been circulating in this
newsgroup then it will tell you the stepping level of your Pentium.

For P90s this level so far has always been 1 or 2.  From the few results
that have been posted, it looks like the step 1 chips were still shipping
at the end of September while the step 2 chips started shipping before
the end of October.

What this means is that the step 2 chips have some fix that probably
occured in the middle of the summer.  Thus if Intel fixed a problem in
the FDIV instruction in the summer it probably isn't the one that
everyone is finding now.

This may also explain why Intel hasn't made a public announcment.  They
won't until they can say that they are shipping fixed chips.

