I will believe Intel fixed the bug only when I see someone, not affiliated
with Intel at all, verify it.  Right now, I have my doubts about whether or
not they fixed it.

I have been thinking about buying a new motherboard recently, and getting a
DX2 processor.  I have decided, because of Intel's attitude towards this,
that I will NOT buy an Intel part, but will probably buy an AMD one instead.


